{"parse":{"title":"cheese","pageid":7340,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Cheese}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n[[Image:Cheese market Basel.jpg|thumb|right|'''Cheese''' for sale in a market.]]\n[[Image:Feta Greece 2.jpg|thumb|right|Feta, a Greek '''cheese'''.]]\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|chēz}}, {{IPA|en|/t͡ʃiːz/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/t͡ʃiz/|a=GA}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-cheese.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-cheese.wav|a=GA}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iːz|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|en|qis}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymon|en|id=dairy product|:inh|enm:chese<id:cheese>|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|chese}}, from [[Anglian]] {{inh|en|ang|ċīese}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*kāsī}}, borrowed from {{der|en|la|cāseus}}. {{doublet|en|queso}}.\n\nCognate with {{cog|stq|Síes|t=cheese}}, {{cog|fy|tsiis|t=cheese}}, {{cog|nl|kaas|t=cheese}}, {{cog|nds-de|Kees|t=cheese}}, {{cog|de|Käse|t=cheese}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~|s|cheesen<l:archaic>}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q10943}}{{lb|en|uncountable}} A [[dairy]] product made from [[curdle]]d or [[culture]]d [[milk]].\n# {{lb|en|countable}} Any particular variety of cheese.\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A piece of cheese, especially one moulded into a large round shape during manufacture.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1951|author={{w|John Wyndham}}|title={{w|The Day of the Triffids}}|publisher=Penguin Books|year_published=1954|location=Harmondsworth|page=153|passage=He had a gloating expression on his face, and was perseveringly rolling a large '''cheese''' along the middle of the road.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=August 2015|title=Mechanism and control of the eye formation in cheese|author=Dominik Guggisberg; et al.|journal=International Dairy Journal|volume=47|pages=118–127|publisher=w:Elsevier|doi=10.1016/j.idairyj.2015.03.001|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0958694615000631|passage=In the tomographic images of the 30-day-old '''cheeses''', the gantry had to be removed with image processing techniques: first, the binarised image (grey level larger than 10<sup>4</sup>) was eroded with a disk of three pixels.}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|United Kingdom}} A thick variety of [[jam]] (fruit preserve), as distinguished from a thinner variety (sometimes called [[jelly]])\n#* '''1807''', Nutt, F. (1807). ''The Complete Confectioner: Or, The Whole Art of Confectionary Made Easy: Containing, Among a Variety of Useful Matter, the Art of Making the Various Kinds of Biscuits, Drops ... as Also the Most Approved Method of Making Cheeses, Puddings, Cakes &c. in 250 Cheap and Fashionable Receipts. The Result of Many Years Experience with the Celebrated Negri and Witten. United Kingdom: reprinted, for Richard Scott and sold at his bookstore, no. 243 Pearl-street.''\n#*: p.82-3, No.244. Damson '''Cheese''': “Pick the damsons free from stalks···You may make plum or bullace '''cheese''' in the same way···”\n# A substance resembling cream cheese, such as [[lemon cheese]]\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|colloquial}} That which is [[melodramatic]], overly [[emotional]], or [[cliché]], i.e. [[cheesy]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012| title=Action Movie Freak| author=Katrina Hill| page=117| passage=It's time to add some '''cheese''' to this action burger! Every genre has them, everybody loves them ... it's the parodies!}}\n#* {{quote-web| en| date=2012-06-18| author=Ryan Lambie| title=10 delightfully cheesy 90s sci-fi movie trailers| work=Den of Geek!| url=http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/90s-trailers/21696/10-delightfully-cheesy-90s-sci-fi-movie-trailers| passage=A film ostensibly about the lead singer of a hair metal band killing innocent people on a future planet Earth, Alienator is the epitome of low-budget '''cheese'''.| accessdate=18 July 2017| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170707052628/http://www.denofgeek.com/movies/90s-trailers/21696/10-delightfully-cheesy-90s-sci-fi-movie-trailers| archivedate=7 July 2017}}\n# {{senseid|en|Q1368}} {{lb|en|uncountable|slang}} [[money#English:_Q1368|Money]].\n#: {{syn|en|cheddar}}\n# {{lb|en|countable|UK}} In [[skittles]], the roughly [[ovoid]] object that is thrown to knock down the skittles.\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|slang|baseball}} A [[fastball]].\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|slang}} A dangerous mixture of black tar [[heroin]] and crushed [[Tylenol|Tylenol PM]] tablets. The resulting powder resembles grated cheese and is snorted.\n# {{lb|en|vulgar|slang}} [[smegma|Smegma]].\n# {{lb|en|technology}} [[hole|Holed]] pattern of [[circuitry]] to decrease pattern density.\n#* '''2006''', US Patent 7458053, International Business Machines Corporation\n#*: It is known in the art to insert features that are electrically inactive (“fill structures”) into a layout to increase layout pattern density or and to remove features from the layout (“'''cheese''' structures”) to decrease layout pattern density.\n# A mass of [[pomace]], or ground apples, pressed together in the shape of a cheese.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2011| author=P. Rutledge| editor=D. Arthey; P.R. Ashurst| title=Fruit Processing| chapter=Production of Non-Fermented Fruit Products| isbn=9781461521037| page=77| passage=Apple pulp is poured into the cloth until the frame is full. The edges of the cloth are folded over the pulp forming a cloth-bound bed of apple pulp, called a ''''cheese'''' as it resembles the European-style bound '''cheese'''. The frame is removed, a divider is placed on the ''''cheese'''' and another ''''cheese'''' is built on top of the first, and so on.}}\n# The flat, circular, [[mucilaginous]] [[fruit]] of {{vern|dwarf mallow}} ({{taxlink|Malva rotundifolia|species}}) or [[marshmallow]] ({{taxfmt|Althaea officinalis|species}}).\n# A low [[curtsey]]; so called on account of the cheese shape assumed by a woman's dress when she stoops after extending the skirts by a rapid gyration.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1853| author=w:Thomas De Quincey| chapter=I Enter the World| title=w:Autobiographic Sketches| passage=The time was morning; the young lady was not fifteen; her spirits were as the spirits of a fawn in May; her ''tour'' of duty for the day was either not come, or was gone; and, finding herself alone in a spacious room, what more reasonable thing could she do than amuse herself with ''making '''cheeses'''?'' that is, whirling round, according to a fashion practised by young ladies both in France and England, and pirouetting until the petticoat is inflated like a balloon, and then sinking into a courtesy.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1857| author=w:William Makepeace Thackeray| title=w:The Virginians| chapter=34| passage=\"I thank your ladyship, I don't like tanzing, and I don't like cards,\" says Miss Hester, tossing up her head; and, dropping a curtsey like a \"'''cheese''',\" she strutted away from the Countess's table.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1897|author=Stanley John Weyman|chapter=The Deanery Ball|title=For the Cause|passage=Mrs. Curzon-Bowlby, thus deserted in the middle of the room, dropped the prettiest of \"'''cheeses''',\" and broke into a merry peal of unaffected laughter.}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n* {{s|product}} {{see thesaurus|en|cheese}}\n* {{s|money}} {{see thesaurus|en|money}}\n\n=====Antonyms=====\n* {{as|circuitry}} {{l|en|fill||dummy pattern to increase pattern density}}\n\n=====Hyponyms=====\n* {{s|dairy product}} {{see thesaurus|en|cheese}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col4|en|cheese antenna|fromunda cheese|rennet cheese|cheese tax\n|Abertam cheese|apple cheese|cheese fries|cheese pizza|goat's-milk cheese|suck cheese|Šar cheese\n|a little bit of bread and no cheese|bread cheese|American cheese|cheese out|cheese scoop|corn cheese|Jack cheese\n|apple-cheese|cheese toastie|cheese with your wine|cheese trier|cheese wiener\n|Añejo cheese|the second mouse gets the cheese|chaffle|cheesable|cheeseball|cheesebox|cheesedick|Cheesefare|cheesefest|cheesehamburger|cheesehead|cheeselep|cheeseless|cheeselicious|cheeselike|cheesemaking|cheeseman|cheesepare|cheesesteak|cheesetastic|cheesevat|cheeseware|